  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Humanitarian Assistance to Vulnerable Earthquake-affected Families of Ecuador</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">On April 16, an earthquake of 7.8 on the scale of Richter hit Ecuador (depth 10 km). The epicentre was in front of the coast between the provinces of Esmeralda and Manabi, close to Muisne, between the municipalities of Cojimies and Pedernales.
The population faces a shortage of food, clean drinking water and is in need of non-food items as well as psychosocial assistance.  Many people do not want to move to reception centres out of fear of looting or because they are still searching for survivors. In the meantime they live and sleep in improvised shelters or on the street, but fear for the frequent aftershocks.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">water storage, water filtration and household NFI for 500 families (ca. 2,500 people) in Municipalities of Pedernales, Jama, Sucre, Chone, Bolivar, El Carmen in Manabi Province
To be implemented by local partner FEPP</narrative>
  </description>
